==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inception
<hw>In*cep"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inceptio</ets>, fr. <ets>incipere</ets> to begin; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>capere</ets> to take. See
<er>Capable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Beginning; commencement; initiation.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Marked with vivacity of <qex>inception</qex>, apathy of progress,
and prematureness of decay.</q> <rj><qau>Rawle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Reception; a taking in.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Poe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inceptive</ent>⟦br⟧
